## Day 19 – Common String Methods in Java

- `length()` → returns number of characters.
- `toUpperCase()` / `toLowerCase()`
- `charAt(index)` → returns character at given position.
- `equals()` → compares two strings.
- `contains()` → checks if a substring exists.
- `substring(start, end)` → part of string.

Example:
```java
String s = "GitHub";
System.out.println(s.length());        // 6
System.out.println(s.toUpperCase());   // GITHUB
System.out.println(s.charAt(0));       // G
System.out.println(s.contains("Hub")); // true
